# Write the Agentic Memory System Vision ADR

## Question

Joel's condition on the constrained proof: the VISION stays clear and part of the design process. Write it down as a durable decision record — the distributed, multi-agent, multi-machine, agentic-first second brain:

- The substrate insight verbatim: the network of Git repositories; dark-wizard as the user brain (union of Joel's user across machines); project brains per repo; machine checkouts as divergeable replicas; repo@machine as a query dimension; divergence as data.
- The Mastra memory mapping ([mastra.ai/docs/memory/overview](https://mastra.ai/docs/memory/overview)): what in joelclaw plays message history (sessions/transcripts), working memory, semantic recall (Typesense), and observational memory (bugle observations → durable Brain pages) — and which layers exist today versus are aspiration.
- The read/write split this map committed to: graph surface first, active observation processing as a follow-on charted map.
- The dual purpose: working memory system and demo content for the overbuilt-second-brain video — demoability as a design constraint.

Draft AFK from this map's grilling record; Joel reviews. Lands where architecture decisions live (`.brain/resources/decisions/` here or joelclaw-wiki's Brain — follow `/skill:brain-first-workflow`). Resolved when the ADR is committed and linked from this map's Notes.

## Resolution (2026-07-12)

Drafted by pi worker Otto (wJ:p3), rendered onto the paper at https://brain.joelclaw.com/decisions/agentic-memory-vision.html, and reviewed by Joel against that page the same day. "Mostly in line," plus two amendments now folded into the accepted ADR ([agentic-memory-system-vision](../../resources/decisions/agentic-memory-system-vision.svx), status `accepted`):

1. **Agent sessions are first-class memory surface**, not just evidence under the system — "basically a guide of what has changed recently and how, with deep intent." `.brain` pages are the neurons (durable state); sessions are the recent activity that explains that state; Typesense already indexes them.
2. **The destination is sharpened**: master a Mastra-style memory system whose observational layer distills Typesense + Brain docs + session history into recall that works — "every context we run in has the ability to understand all of the work that we're doing." Functional bar, not architectural.

Both amendments flow forward as the stated bar for the graph/Typesense boundary grilling and the follow-on write-loop map.
